title.20: Peter Parker, the Spectacular Spider-Man Annual (1979) #11
title.52: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger (1988) #19

description.0: Xavier enters Muir Island and discovers both the X-Factor and the free X-Men are being held in a telekinetic force by Legion!
description.1: Wolvie has an epic, Times Square battle! Will there be civilian casualties?
description.5: What if Captain America formed the Avengers? Having never been stuck in ice, Steve Rogers forms the Avengers. But what is the deadly secret behind President Steve Rogers and can the Avengers save the country when it's revealed?
description.7: Spider-Man/Nova team-up! After interrupting a robbery, Spider-Man inadvertently ignites the rage of far sinister forces. Enter the Tri-Sentinel, man killer robot of the Life Foundation!
description.8: The Avengers face defeat at the hands of the Brethren. Crystal of the Inhumans is allowed to join the team at the request of Quicksilver. Sybil Dorn, lover of Thane Ector, attacks Sersi in a fit of rage! Plus, the origin of the Brethren revealed!
description.9: Superia seeks to turn Captain America and Paladin into women! Plus: the future of America is revealed!
description.21: THE VIBRANIUM VENDETTA PART 3 It all concludes, (and explodes), here! Spider-Man is joined by Avengers Iron Man and Black Panther to take down Ultron. But when facing a foe as difficult as the automaton, expect the unexpected! Spider-Man is in for the battle of his life, and even Earth’s Mightiest Heroes may not provide the back-up he needs.
description.23: She-Hulk and Louise investigate a moving mountain after a professor claims it's a living hill he has encountered in Transylvania!
description.24: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith. WEAPON X The Professor has Logan dead to rights. But do you kill the unkillable?
description.25: Cap and Paladin face off against the super powered women army! Find out what the Femizons have planned for Steve Rogers and Paladin!
description.26: Logan reflects and has a gruesome flashback to a battle with one of his worst foes…
description.27: DEATH TO THE EMPEROR! With the help of Silver Surfer, the Kree agrees to a change-up in leadership.
description.28: Thane takes Sersi hostage, but quickly discovers romantic interest in his prisoner. The other team members continue to search through the Collector's ecosystems. Will this be the final battle between the Avengers and Thane Ector?
description.29: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith. WEAPON X Logan has caught up to his prey. Will any of the members of Experiment X make it out alive?
description.32: WHILE A UNIVERSE TREMBLES! Drax has bigger problems to worry about than Firelord when Doctor Strange unites a group of heroes to prepare for a galactic battle with none other than...THANOS!
description.34: Silver Dagger comes for what is rightfully his…something in the possession of none other than Doctor Strange!
description.37: Guest-starring Ghost Rider! The Hand are taking New York City's elite in plain sight, and the Man Without Fear must team with the Spirit of Vengeance to stop them!
description.39: The Hulk has been shrunken down to six inches! Will this miniaturized Hulk be able to save Nadia Blonsky before the Abomination whisks her away to an unknown fate?
description.40: Jim Rhodes as Iron Man battles the deadly Fin Fang Foom! But the armored suit is no match for the ancient alien. Will Tony Stark watch helplessly as his friend dies in his place?
description.41: Before Eric can get the answers about Thor he's looking for, an ancient and cosmic evil descends upon Asgard - Annihilus!
description.45: A solo story starring the ever-lovin' blue-eyed Thing! Ben Grimm takes a trip down to his old home on Yancy Street, but things quickly get ugly when the Wrecker comes calling!
description.46: Under the mental control of the Shadow King, Colossus chases Xavier and Stevie Hunter through the ruins of the Xavier Institute.
description.47: Wolverine needs Nick Fury's help to discover crucial (and missing) parts of his past. Unfortunately, Wolvie finds out that information is "classified…"
description.49: Spider-Man faces imminent Doom! Black Fox has stolen one of Doctor Doom's family heirlooms, and Spidey has 24 hours to collect- or else!
description.50: The Avengers take on Thane Ector and his villainous Brethren! In battle, Captain America takes several unexpected blows, while the rest of the team must restore the Collector's health. A battle on the Blue Side of the Moon that no fan should miss!
description.51: The battle against the Femizons continues! Diamondback learns that the life of a super hero is never easy! Find out her shocking decision when she finally reaches a crossroads!
description.53: What insanity has come to She-Hulk that she finds herself battling Apocalypse, Sabretooth, Master Mold, Juggernaut, Rhino and more?! And what do UFOs have to do with it?
description.62: What if Captain America led an army of super-soldiers in WWII? In this universe, Steve Rogers is able to save the life of Dr. Erskine, the creator of the super-soldier formula. Instead of being the only super-soldier, Steve Rogers becomes just one of many to fight the Axis powers in WWII. Post-war, Rogers becomes President of the United States, but what sinister secret does he hold?
description.70: M.O.D.A.M. has formed together her team of evil super-powered villainesses! First on her list: Diamondback!
description.71: Elsie Dee attempts to save Wolverine's life at the cost of her own. That's brave and touching, but Sabretooth doesn't give a damn. He wants to drag Wolverine down with him.
description.72: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.
description.73: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.
description.75: Nova must face her toughest enemy yet: her guilty conscience over being a herald to Galactus!
description.77: Doctor Strange enters the dark depths of the Silver Surfer's mind! There he must restore the Surfer's inner psyche to a healthy state. After all, Strange needs him.
description.78: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith. WEAPON X How reliable is data culled from Logan's battles with wildlife? If the Professor and Cornelius want to see how sharp their knife is, they'll need to put Logan on the scent of the most dangerous game…
description.79: Matt and Karen retread old ground in their relationship with no reconciliation. Kingpin makes his network move.
description.81: The Abomination kidnaps his ex-wife- and Hulk's not standing for it!
description.82: One of the biggest events ever to hit the Marvel Universe! For Thanos, the Infinity Gauntlet was the ultimate prize to be coveted above all else. With it came omnipotence. Now it's up to Earth's super heroes to make a desperate attempt to thwart this mad god's insane plunge into galactic self-destruction.
description.83: The time has finally come! It's the big showdown between Iron Man and the Mandarin. Only, Tony Stark won't be awake to see it!
description.84: Eric Masterson is the all-new Thor! But what happened to the original Thunder God?
description.88: Prison break in the timestream! The FF fights for their freedom from the Time Variance Authority, but what secrets are the timekeeping corps hiding?
description.89: The Shadow King and Dr. Lian Shen watch various forms of hate taking place across the world. The Shadow King vows that he will destroy Xavier and the X-Men once and for all.
description.90: Wolverine, recovering from major injuries whilst in a sewer, has to now battle Sabretooth at full strength.
description.94: What if the Sub-Mariner had joined the Fantastic Four? When the Human Torch leaves the FF, the Invisible Woman convinces Namor to join the team. But will this lead Sue to turn her affections away from Reed and towards Namor? And will Doctor Doom use the team's new uncertainty to finally destroy them for good?
description.97: The wily Black Fox is at it again! And this time, the mastermind thief's stolen the Trask diamond! Will Spidey be able to restore the gem to its rightful owner...and contend with a surprise villain?
description.98: Karnak and Quicksilver discovered in deep space! What is the mysterious vessel that has held them hostage for so long? And why is the Collector a prisoner in his own ship?
description.99: Don't miss this all-new action-packed issue as Captain America finds himself at the mercy of M.O.D.A.M.!

1.text: Wolvie has an epic, Times Square battle! Will there be civilian casualties?

3.text: Spider-Woman, Julia Carpenter joins the team!

10.text: The earth-shattering saga rages on! Darkhawk continues to fight the good fight, but at what cost?

11.text: The Guardians and the Force fight side by side against Protégé!

12.text: THE SOULS OF CYBER-FOLK PART 2 Will Deathlok be able to save Misty Knight from the clutches of Doctor Doom? A battle to near-death ensues between a cyborg and a master of mystical arts! This is a can’t-miss conflict you have to see to believe!

13.text: GeneTech’s supervillain team returns for more! Will the New Warriors be able to square off with Psionex for a  second round? Plus, just what kind of trouble has GeneTech fallen into? And why are they counting on the New Warriors for a bailout?

15.text: A battle against the Iron Fist-impersonating Super-Skrull in the Savage Land!

16.text: Relive the monumental origins of Marvel's Sentinel of Liberty, retold for the modern age -- with new secrets revealed! As Captain America is born, so does the rise of the Red Skull begin…but who is the mysterious Agent X?

17.text: New York is in flames and all Moon Knight can do is save whoever he can. Can there be any redemption for Stained Glass Scarlet after what she's done?

18.text: The impish impossibilities continue as the Impossible Man and his gaggle of Poppupian progeny continue their summer vacation on Earth…and Realms Beyond! The whole gang takes off for the Savage Land and Asgard!

19.text: Spidey learns the difference between Johnny Blaze's Ghost Rider and Danny Ketch's...and he may not like it!

20.text: The Vibranium Vendetta continues as Spider-Man prevents Wakanda’s most valuable resource from falling into Roxxon’s hands. The Sunturion is determined to eliminate Spider-Man, and acquire a Vibranium for his shadowy employer. Plus, a flashback story featuring young Peter’s adventures in babysitting!

21.text: THE VIBRANIUM VENDETTA PART 3 It all concludes, (and explodes), here! Spider-Man is joined by Avengers Iron Man and Black Panther to take down Ultron. But when facing a foe as difficult as the automaton, expect the unexpected! Spider-Man is in for the battle of his life, and even Earth’s Mightiest Heroes may not provide the back-up he needs.

22.text: Cosmic co-stars! Silver Surfer becomes an ally to Damage Control in the wake of Galactus. Appearances by Lord Chaos and Master Order, the In-Betweener, and even…Death!

23.text: She-Hulk and Louise investigate a moving mountain after a professor claims it's a living hill he has encountered in Transylvania!

24.text: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.

26.text: Logan reflects and has a gruesome flashback to a battle with one of his worst foes…

27.text: DEATH TO THE EMPEROR! With the help of Silver Surfer, the Kree agrees to a change-up in leadership.

29.text: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.

30.text:
Billions of people across the planet have disappeared; now, the super
humans of Earth scramble to find out what's going on! Featuring Quasar!
Dr. Strange! Dr. Doom! Captain America! Thor! Warlock! Wolverine! Iron
Man! She-Hulk! The Silver Surfer! And more!

31.text: SUB-CITY, Part One! Spider-Man is back in black in this special issue! What dastardly plot has Morbius concocted?

32.text: WHILE A UNIVERSE TREMBLES! Drax has bigger problems to worry about than Firelord when Doctor Strange unites a group of heroes to prepare for a galactic battle with none other than...THANOS!

33.text: X-Force sets out on their first mission! To defeat the MLF and to stop the terrorist called Stryfe, the team heads to Antarctica!

34.text: Silver Dagger comes for what is rightfully his…something in the possession of none other than Doctor Strange!

35.text: The Avengers and Fantastic Four guest-star, helping Nick Fury pick up the pieces after Hydra’s attack. Baron Strucker makes a startling revelation about S.H.I.E.L.D.’s early history. Wolverine sharpens his claws for war!

36.text: Ghost Rider and Spider-Man face off against Hobgoblin!

38.text: Lockheed’s on the astral plane! While clinging to life, Kitty Pryde’s dragon sidekick has an out-of-body experience that sees him soar to the cosmos and beyond!

43.text: The Shadow King has taken over the minds of the X-Men! Can they escape the mind control without any help?

47.text: Wolverine needs Nick Fury's help to discover crucial (and missing) parts of his past. Unfortunately, Wolvie finds out that information is "classified…"

52.text: The true, unadulterated origin of Cloak and Dagger revealed!

53.text: What insanity has come to She-Hulk that she finds herself battling Apocalypse, Sabretooth, Master Mold, Juggernaut, Rhino, and more?! And what do UFOs have to do with it?

55.text: Edifice Rex catches the eye of Galactus. Is this too big a mess for Damage Control? Plus, is the public ready for Damage Control: The Movie?

56.text: Darkhawk teams up with Captain America and Daredevil to fight the U-Foes!

57.text: The Guardians must take on multiple threats at once. And the secret of Replica’s shape-changing powers is revealed!

58.text: THE SOULS OF CYBER-FOLK PART 1 Guest-starring the X-Man, Forge! Deathlok squares off with the Capturebots after Forge and Misty Knight are nearly kidnapped. Why are the Capturebots after cyborgs? And will Deathlok and Misty Knight be able to save Forge?

59.text: Deep below the ocean’s surface, Namorita does battle with the Sea Urchin! Will Namor’s cousin be able to stand alone against her greatest foe yet? Sub-Mariner and Darkhawk guest-star!

60.text: THE KINGS OF PAIN PART 2.  A chock-full annual issue! The newly minted X-Force, (previously the New Mutants), continues to smack down with the New Warriors. But will the teams be able to set aside their differences when they discover a common agenda? Plus, each member of the New Warriors shares their origin story!

61.text: Tigra is the latest Avenger to be in critical condition. Will she be able to survive her deep knife wound?

63.text: Battle in Oblivion! Both serving as avatars of two powerful cosmic beings, Quasar and Maelstrom must duke it out for the fate of the universe. And when the dust settles, one of Quasar’s closest comrades stands to be resurrected…

66.text: Wolverine and Wolfsbane are finally back in their own bodies. Now it's time to fight the Sorcerer in order to get back home.

67.text: The Super-Skrull has taken Namor hostage!

68.text: Spider-Man vs. the Sinister Syndicate -- the FINAL SHOWDOWN! The odds don't look good for the Wall-Crawler…but that's never stopped Spidey before!

69.text: The secret history of Stained Glass Scarlet revealed!

71.text: Elsie Dee attempts to save Wolverine's life at the cost of her own. That's brave and touching, but Sabretooth doesn't give a damn. He wants to drag Wolverine down with him.

72.text: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.

73.text: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.

74.text: Now Wolverine and Spider-Man are protecting Wendigo?! The tables have turned in this strange issue. Guest-starring Puck and Sasquatch of Alpha Flight!

75.text: Nova must face her toughest enemy yet: her guilty conscience over being a herald to Galactus!

76.text: Nick Fury may be losing his mind- at least that’s what his closest comrades believe! S.H.I.E.L.D.’s leadership comes under question after Hydra successfully attacks S.H.I.E.L.D.’s headquarters! Has Nick Fury finally cracked?

77.text: Doctor Strange enters the dark depths of the Silver Surfer's mind! There he must restore the Surfer's inner psyche to a healthy state. After all, Strange needs him.

78.text: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.

80.text: Finally, a team-up! Excalibur sets aside differences with the West Coast Avengers to travel to Limbo and back…all to put the kibosh on Doctor Doom and his demon horde army!

82.text:
Seeking to impress the Mistress Death, who returned him to life, Thanos
has gained control over the Infinity Gauntlet -- making him an
all-powerful god! With Mephisto as his familiar, Thanos wipes out half
of the life in the universe with a snap of his fingers! What will Earth
do when half its the heroes are killed?
One of the most epic Marvel stories ever told deserves a cover that does it justice.  George Perez delivers in spades.

86.text: When Nathan is infected with a fatal virus by Apocalypse, Scott knows there is only one thing he can do to save his son.

90.text: Wolverine, recovering from major injuries whilst in a sewer, has to now battle Sabretooth at full strength.

95.text: Doctor Strange leads the defense against Maelstrom’s “new spin” on Earth. While the universe threatens to implode, Quasar meets with Infinity in the Quantum Zone.
